The test program works as follows.

Create two directories, say ``foo'' and ``bar'', containg ``runme''
scripts as per spec.  Then run

test-pousse -n <n> foo bar

<n> is 10 by default.  The program plays a complete game and
prints the winner. 


HUMAN MODE:

test-pousse -h -n <n> program

will let you play with the computer.  Enter your move, or

flip:  flip sides
back:  revoke move


